The Other Side of the Gate

83
00:04:35,370 --> 00:04:36,750
Edward-san!

84
00:04:37,940 --> 00:04:39,350
What were you doing?

85
00:04:39,350 --> 00:04:42,530
Sorry. Is this the place?

86
00:04:42,530 --> 00:04:45,100
Yes. This is definitely the place.

87
00:04:45,100 --> 00:04:47,090
Show me one more time.

88
00:04:48,850 --> 00:04:54,600
Dad once came here to Central, 
looking for a way to refine the red water.

89
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:59,110
He wound up going to a place called the 5th Laboratory,

90
00:04:59,460 --> 00:05:02,560
and there, he met up 
with a certain alchemist.

91
00:05:04,810 --> 00:05:09,400
That person told him that there was some indispensable element

92
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:12,870
that was necessary to transmute the red water 
all the way into a Philosopher's Stone

93
00:05:12,870 --> 00:05:15,520
and hinted to him 
that it was human lives.

94
00:05:15,520 --> 00:05:18,380
He also showed him 
where the real laboratory was.

95
00:05:20,420 --> 00:05:24,000
The 5th Laboratory was nothing more than a secret entrance.

96
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:27,720
In fact, there was an even larger human experimentation lab.

97
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:31,460
This does indeed appear to be the place that we have been searching for.

98
00:05:33,150 --> 00:05:34,760
I'm going alone.

99
00:05:34,760 --> 00:05:38,440
But Al-kun is in danger, 
though we don't know what kind, right?

100
00:05:39,340 --> 00:05:43,280
It's all right. He's just 
gotten a little lost. That's all.

101
00:05:48,120 --> 00:05:48,780
Ed...

102
00:05:51,720 --> 00:05:54,180
The reason why we showed you what was in this journal...

103
00:05:54,180 --> 00:05:56,870
was not because we wanted you to make a Philosopher's Stone.

104
00:05:57,840 --> 00:06:02,010
I know. I'm not going there 
to create a Philosopher's Stone.

105
00:06:02,010 --> 00:06:03,100
Believe me.

106
00:06:14,730 --> 00:06:16,650
Come back to us now!

107
00:06:16,650 --> 00:06:18,350
Come back to us alive!

108
00:06:32,200 --> 00:06:34,110
According to Dad's journal,

109
00:06:34,110 --> 00:06:36,520
you descend from the temple of the ancient religion

110
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:39,490
and go farther and farther underground, 
and then suddenly...

111
00:06:42,290 --> 00:06:46,920
there's another city, 
all tucked away beneath Central.

112
00:06:47,680 --> 00:06:49,990
Dad said that judging by its style of architecture,

113
00:06:49,990 --> 00:06:52,930
it looked like the city was nearly four hundred years old.

114
00:06:53,770 --> 00:06:56,240
There's a legend that says 
that the city that was there,

115
00:06:56,240 --> 00:06:58,720
where Central is now, 
vanished overnight.

116
00:07:00,270 --> 00:07:04,370
Dad says he thought that there might have been alchemists who were performing

117
00:07:04,370 --> 00:07:09,860
some kind of experiment and may have closed up the whole city underground.

118
00:07:12,090 --> 00:07:14,910
The people of the city 
were all sacrificed

119
00:07:14,910 --> 00:07:17,200
to be used in their 
Philosopher's Stone.

120
00:07:17,850 --> 00:07:21,860
And then, to hide the fact that there weren't any people left,

121
00:07:21,860 --> 00:07:24,710
they made the city itself disappear.

122
00:07:25,000 --> 00:07:28,310
There's actually someone who thought that up?

123
00:07:30,130 --> 00:07:31,930
Is anyone there?!

124
00:07:35,240 --> 00:07:38,560
I know you're here! You knew about everything, didn't you,

125
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:41,060
Pop?!

126
00:07:47,580 --> 00:07:49,270
No, Gluttony.

127
00:07:49,830 --> 00:07:51,120
Be patient.

128
00:07:54,540 --> 00:07:57,260
This girl's body is 
very important, after all.

129
00:08:00,010 --> 00:08:05,250
So pretty. It's no wonder why Ed and Al would like you.

130
00:08:05,970 --> 00:08:09,260
They <i>are</i> his children.

131
00:08:09,260 --> 00:08:11,470
Hey, what happened to Lust?!

132
00:08:12,260 --> 00:08:14,590
Yes, what could have 
happened to her?

133
00:08:14,590 --> 00:08:17,250
That's right, I need to 
get my dress ready.

134
00:08:18,200 --> 00:08:20,630
We have to be pretty 
when we greet him.

135
00:08:21,180 --> 00:08:22,480
Somebody's here.

136
00:08:23,350 --> 00:08:25,480
My, that was quick.

137
00:08:27,890 --> 00:08:28,730
Where is he?

138
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:29,920
Wrath...

139
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:29,920
Where is he?!

140
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:31,320
What a pest!

141
00:08:30,540 --> 00:08:32,430
Where's the Philosopher's Stone?!

142
00:08:31,320 --> 00:08:33,300
What's the meaning of this?

143
00:08:32,430 --> 00:08:35,160
Where is he?! Where did he go?!

144
00:08:33,300 --> 00:08:35,950
I thought he was keeping an eye on Edward.

145
00:08:35,160 --> 00:08:38,330
Tell me, Envy! Please!

146
00:08:35,950 --> 00:08:38,330
That's what I thought I told him to do.

147
00:08:38,330 --> 00:08:40,410
Please! Give me the 
Philosopher's Stone, quick!

148
00:08:40,410 --> 00:08:44,350
Wrath, you have to be a good boy, 
or I won't make you human.

149
00:08:44,350 --> 00:08:45,920
There's no time for that!

150
00:08:45,920 --> 00:08:47,920
Mama... Mama is going to be all gone!

151
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:49,080
Mama?

152
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:51,300
He means Sloth.

153
00:08:51,300 --> 00:08:54,120
Sloth is not your mama.

154
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:56,410
Homunculi do not have mothers.

155
00:08:56,410 --> 00:08:58,430
Bring Mama back to life! Please!

156
00:08:59,750 --> 00:09:01,930
Don't talk like you're human.

157
00:09:01,930 --> 00:09:03,810
Mama... Mama!

158
00:09:03,810 --> 00:09:05,550
Mama!

159
00:09:05,550 --> 00:09:06,310
Envy!

160
00:09:09,330 --> 00:09:11,190
Please!

161
00:09:17,530 --> 00:09:20,030
What do you think 
you can do in your shape?

162
00:09:30,100 --> 00:09:32,140
What power!

163
00:09:32,140 --> 00:09:36,220
It's only natural that 
Edward Elric would use Automail.

164
00:09:36,220 --> 00:09:37,590
This is fun!

165
00:09:38,110 --> 00:09:40,440
Someone like you is a soldier?

166
00:09:40,440 --> 00:09:42,810
That explains why no one has realized who the Führer is!

167
00:09:43,230 --> 00:09:47,020
It's still not too late for you. Become one of my soldiers.

168
00:09:48,340 --> 00:09:52,760
We are ready to wage war on 
the north, the west, and the south.

169
00:09:52,760 --> 00:09:55,150
The time has come for 
the continent to be united.

170
00:09:56,150 --> 00:09:57,530
Not interested.

171
00:09:57,790 --> 00:09:59,450
In that case, die!

172
00:10:09,170 --> 00:10:11,600
Your pupils will be 
following you soon as well.

173
00:10:14,250 --> 00:10:16,050
What are you doing?! 
I am your superior officer!

174
00:10:17,630 --> 00:10:19,110
You too?!

175
00:10:19,760 --> 00:10:21,000
Izumi-san!

176
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,760
Where's... Ed?

177
00:10:24,170 --> 00:10:27,100
By now, both brothers should be at the place that was written about in that journal.

178
00:10:29,600 --> 00:10:33,610
You all believed... in those boys?

179
00:10:34,530 --> 00:10:38,600
Believing in and protecting children 
is the job of an adult.

180
00:10:39,420 --> 00:10:41,370
That's what someone once told me.

181
00:11:17,980 --> 00:11:18,900
Rose?

182
00:11:24,250 --> 00:11:25,340
Ed...

183
00:11:26,830 --> 00:11:28,910
You finally came.

184
00:11:32,770 --> 00:11:35,300
Now, that should 
teach you a lesson.

185
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:37,550
Don't start any fights 
with these guys.

186
00:11:39,070 --> 00:11:42,210
You really don't ever learn 
unless you get hurt.

187
00:11:43,680 --> 00:11:44,680
Something the matter?

188
00:11:45,960 --> 00:11:48,680
I think I just figured something out.

189
00:11:49,520 --> 00:11:50,680
Figured what out?

190
00:11:51,380 --> 00:11:54,660
Hughes-san said something 
before he died.

191
00:11:54,660 --> 00:11:57,480
"What if everything was backwards?"

192
00:11:57,480 --> 00:11:59,790
I never understood what he meant.

193
00:11:59,790 --> 00:12:01,400
And you figured it out?

194
00:12:01,400 --> 00:12:07,910
We've been thinking that the homunculi 
were trying to create a Philosopher's Stone.

195
00:12:07,910 --> 00:12:10,660
But what if it was 
the other way around?

196
00:12:11,340 --> 00:12:14,270
They wait until it is just barely completed, and then take it away.

197
00:12:14,270 --> 00:12:17,560
Then they eliminate everyone 
who can prove it ever happened.

198
00:12:17,560 --> 00:12:21,590
What's left is a rumor that says if you come near the Philosopher's Stone, you'll be destroyed.

199
00:12:21,590 --> 00:12:24,640
In time, people become afraid of the Philosopher's Stone...

200
00:12:25,420 --> 00:12:28,780
So they'll keep away from it?

201
00:12:28,780 --> 00:12:30,890
But that would almost make them good people, wouldn't it?

202
00:12:30,890 --> 00:12:34,110
They're making sure people stay out of danger, after all.

203
00:12:35,780 --> 00:12:36,900
What's more,

204
00:12:36,900 --> 00:12:38,900
no matter how dangerous it is,

205
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:43,000
I'll bet that people will 
still go on looking for it.

206
00:12:45,170 --> 00:12:47,920
I wonder how Edward-san and his brother are doing.

207
00:12:47,920 --> 00:12:49,910
I'm sure they're getting along fine.

208
00:12:49,910 --> 00:12:51,400
That much is certain.

209
00:12:53,790 --> 00:12:56,590
Pain that teaches a lesson, huh?

210
00:12:56,590 --> 00:13:00,510
But God is the only one who can teach that kind of lesson.

211
00:13:05,930 --> 00:13:08,640
R-Rose, what are you doing here?

212
00:13:08,900 --> 00:13:12,280
I've been waiting for you 
a long, long time.

213
00:13:12,870 --> 00:13:14,640
Ed, I...

214
00:13:15,650 --> 00:13:16,710
Rose...

215
00:13:19,770 --> 00:13:22,400
Rose, was Al brought here?

216
00:13:22,830 --> 00:13:24,390
What exactly is this place?

217
00:13:28,350 --> 00:13:29,660
My baby...

218
00:13:34,740 --> 00:13:36,250
My baby...

219
00:13:36,720 --> 00:13:38,970
You should have danced with her.

220
00:13:38,970 --> 00:13:42,750
She's been waiting for you ever since we fled here.

221
00:13:42,750 --> 00:13:43,960
You're despicable.

222
00:13:44,830 --> 00:13:47,470
Lyra, you brought Rose here?

223
00:13:47,840 --> 00:13:51,330
There's an old city that 
only alchemists know of.

224
00:13:51,330 --> 00:13:53,100
That's what Dante-sensei told me.

225
00:13:53,420 --> 00:13:58,670
Speaking of Dante-san, I still 
haven't heard how she was killed.

226
00:13:58,670 --> 00:14:01,760
She was killed by 
that homunculus Greed.

227
00:14:01,760 --> 00:14:02,980
I thought I told you.

228
00:14:02,980 --> 00:14:04,150
That is a lie.

229
00:14:04,790 --> 00:14:05,650
A lie?

230
00:14:05,650 --> 00:14:08,930
The transmutation circle that was left in Dante-san's house

231
00:14:08,930 --> 00:14:12,380
was one that could keep 
a homunculus from moving.

232
00:14:12,380 --> 00:14:16,240
There were bones from the man 
on whom Greed was based.

233
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:19,350
Greed shouldn't have been able to 
take action against Dante-san.

234
00:14:19,350 --> 00:14:23,690
Are you sure? 
Still, Dante-san definitely is dead.

235
00:14:23,690 --> 00:14:25,410
But supposing that what was there

236
00:14:25,410 --> 00:14:28,600
was nothing more than a shell 
that her soul had sloughed off...

237
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:29,930
What are you saying?

238
00:14:29,930 --> 00:14:33,980
Let's suppose there were people who used the power of the Philosopher's Stone

239
00:14:33,980 --> 00:14:36,810
to move from one body to another 
and who have lived for hundreds of years.

240
00:14:37,470 --> 00:14:40,520
Back there, you made it 
look like you were dead

241
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:44,140
and then took over Lyra's body. 
Isn't that right?!

242
00:14:44,140 --> 00:14:46,190
Ed, stop! I am—

243
00:14:56,150 --> 00:14:57,330
That was close.

244
00:14:57,780 --> 00:14:59,900
When did you see the gate, Lyra?

245
00:15:01,810 --> 00:15:04,390
You transmuted without 
using a transmutation circle.

246
00:15:04,390 --> 00:15:06,340
That's my answer, Dante!

247
00:15:07,780 --> 00:15:11,050
When did you figure it out, 
Edward Elric?

248
00:15:11,050 --> 00:15:12,850
Then it's true?

249
00:15:12,850 --> 00:15:15,500
I've really come to like this body.

250
00:15:15,500 --> 00:15:17,560
So then, what number is she?

251
00:15:17,560 --> 00:15:21,190
Who knows? 
It hasn't been ten yet, though.

252
00:15:21,190 --> 00:15:25,190
After all, I have to use the 
Philosopher's Stone each time.

253
00:15:25,450 --> 00:15:29,760
Did you wipe out the residents of this city to make your Philosopher's Stone?

254
00:15:29,760 --> 00:15:33,720
Yes, the same as with the nation to the east, 
which was destroyed overnight.

255
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:36,980
I should mention, though, 
that I was not the one who made them.

256
00:15:36,980 --> 00:15:39,500
Hohenheim of Light...

257
00:15:39,500 --> 00:15:43,260
